The excellent airport connection was particularly important to a global company such as Fujitsu, he added.
Yesterday the coming relocation of an important company in the region was a cause for joy among the winners and disappointment among the losers.
Markus Frank (CDU), head of Frankfurt's economic affairs department, said the city had again attracted a global player,
which was a "fantastic recognition of the city."
